===2010 census===
As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 46 people living in the town. 100.0% were [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]].<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US4536655| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Census Summary File 1 (DP-1): Jenkinsville town, South Carolina| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=August 12, 2016| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213114748/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US4536655| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref>

